{"kind":"cas-record-v1","metadata":{"entries":[{"origin_package":"github.com/codalotl/codalotl/internal/cli","target_package":"github.com/codalotl/codalotl/internal/llmmodel","identifier":"ProviderSubscription","question":"The cli SPEC review mentions using llmmodel/openaisub provider subscription-required state so startup can avoid API-key fallback when saved OpenAI subscription auth exists but is unusable. The public docs I fetched show ProviderSubscription plus Set/Get/Clear, but no obvious subscription-required flag. Is there an exported llmmodel API/state for marking a provider as subscription-required or blocking API-key fallback when saved subscription auth is present but unusable?","answer":"No. In the current `internal/llmmodel` implementation, there is no exported API/state for “subscription required” and no exported mechanism to suppress provider-level API-key fallback when saved subscription auth is present but unusable.\n\nWhat exists now:\n\n- `ProviderSubscription`\n- `SetProviderSubscription(providerID, sub)`\n- `ClearProviderSubscription(providerID)`\n- `GetProviderSubscription(providerID) (ProviderSubscription, bool)`\n- `ProviderHasSubscription(providerID) bool`\n- `AvailableModelIDsWithAuth()`\n\nDocumented/current behavior:\n\n- `GetProviderSubscription` only returns usable subscription auth.\n- Usable means:\n  - requested provider is not unknown\n  - `sub.ProviderID` matches\n  - `AccessToken`, `AccountID`, and `APIEndpointURL` are nonblank\n  - `ExpiresAt` is after `time.Now()`\n- If a saved subscription is expired/malformed, `GetProviderSubscription` returns `(zero, false)`.\n- `ProviderHasSubscription` is just based on `GetProviderSubscription`, so it also only reports usable subscriptions.\n\nImplementation facts:\n\n- `GetAPIKey` does not check subscription state. It still falls back through:\n  1. per-model actual key\n  2. per-model env key\n  3. `ConfigureProviderKey`\n  4. provider default env var\n- `AvailableModelIDsWithAuth` includes a model if `GetAPIKey(id) != \"\" || modelHasEligibleProviderSubscription(id)`.\n- Therefore, if OpenAI has an env/configured API key, unusable saved subscription auth will not block API-key availability.\n\nThe confusing part: `SPEC.md` does mention APIs like `SetProviderSubscriptionRequired`, `ProviderSubscriptionRequired`, and `ModelUsesProviderSubscription`, plus fallback suppression semantics. But those identifiers are not present in the actual exported public API or implementation. So the SPEC appears ahead of/stale relative to the current code.\n\nBottom line: callers cannot currently express “saved OpenAI subscription exists, so do not use API-key fallback unless subscription is usable” through exported `llmmodel` APIs. That would need a new `llmmodel` API/state implementation, or the CLI/openaisub layer must enforce that policy externally."}]},"additional_info":{"unix_timestamp":1780511919,"paths":["internal/llmmodel/SPEC.md","internal/llmmodel/config_embed.go","internal/llmmodel/doc.go","internal/llmmodel/llmmodel.go","internal/llmmodel/llmmodel_test.go"],"git_clean":false,"git_commit":"be348d8e211b39fa18deb989f62fe709d7eb6b36","git_merge_base":"c9903a5cbb1a6cef9a994d6c78a1444b13b70ec3"}}